summary: Since apparently S2 is coming out I just want to say again that it's funny to me that when Aggretsuko was a thing everyone was...
body: Since apparently S2 is coming out I just want to say again that it’s funny to me that when Aggretsuko was a thing everyone was absolutely fine with ignoring the blatant and prevalent ableism in the show to gush over what a ~nice and respectful feminist~ Haida was until the Christmas special happened (which was a special episode entirely about Haida being a clingy, disrespectful womanizer) and everyone just shut up entirely about the show

body:

On June 7, Netflix started streaming a new trailer for the upcoming second season of Aggretsuko. The 100-second promo previews the seasons’s English dub.

Aggretsuko‘s second season will launch on their platform on June 14. Like the first season, the title will be presented as a Netflix Original.

Aggretsuko S2 gets new trailer, releases June 14

A new trailer has been released for the second season of Aggretsuko, which is set to release June 14, 2019.

From her mother meddling in her personal affairs to a nightmarish new coworker, Retsuko’s still got a lot to rage about in her karaoke sessions.
